    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nI have this `numpy` array\n```python\nt = np.dtype([(\"ix\", \"i4\"), (\"val\", \"i4\")])\narray = np.array([(0, 0), (1, 1), (2, 2)], dtype=t)[[\"val\"]]\n```\nIt is unclear how or not possible at all to map this array to cython struct.\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\nimport numpy as np\n\ncdef packed struct Foo:\n  const char _pad[4]\n  const int val\n\ndef bar():\n  cdef const Foo[:] mview\n  \n  t = np.dtype([(\"ix\", \"i4\"), (\"val\", \"i4\")])\n  array = np.array([(0, 0), (1, 1), (2, 2)], dtype=t)[[\"val\"]]\n  print(f\"{array=}\")\n  print(f\"{memoryview(array).format=}\")\n  \n  mview = array\n```\n\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\nThe cython code above should run.\n\n### OS\n\nLinux\n\n### Python version\n\n3.14\n\n### Cython version\n\n3.2.4\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
