    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "If you define the struct as `extern` (so Cython doesn't know about the `_pad` field) then it works:\n\n```\nimport numpy as np\n\ncdef extern from *:\n  \"\"\"\n  __attribute__((__packed__)) struct Foo {\n    char _pad[4];\n    int val;\n  };\n  \"\"\"\n  cdef packed struct Foo:\n    const int val\n\ndef bar():\n  cdef const Foo[:] mview\n  \n  t = np.dtype([(\"ix\", \"i4\"), (\"val\", \"i4\")])\n  array = np.array([(0, 0), (1, 1), (2, 2)], dtype=t)[[\"val\"]]\n  print(f\"{array=}\")\n  print(f\"{memoryview(array).format=}\")\n  \n  mview = array\n```\n\nAlternatively, if you get a non-struct view of it then it works\n\n```\ndef bar():\n  cdef const int[:] mview\n  \n  t = np.dtype([(\"ix\", \"i4\"), (\"val\", \"i4\")])\n  array = np.array([(0, 0), (1, 1), (2, 2)], dtype=t)[\"val\"]  # change here\n  print(f\"{array=}\")\n  print(f\"{memoryview(array).format=}\")\n  \n  mview = array\n```\n\nI don't think there's a way of defining the struct within Cython and then having it ignore the `_pad` field.",
